{
  "doc_id": "47034",
  "text": "Note that the performance of semi-supervised learning algorithms are usually not stable because the unlabeled examples may often be wrongly labeled during the learning process [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . A promising solution to this problem may be using data editing mechanisms, such as the one described in [CITATION_3] , to help identify the wrongly labeled examples. Incorporating data editing mechanisms into tri-training and other semi-supervised learning algorithms is an interesting issue to be investigated in future work.",
